│ An LLVM bug is causing a crash in the loop vectorizer when handling an induction variable  │
│ with a bit-width greater than 64 and a negative step. The crash is due to an assertion     │
│ failure in `APInt::getZExtValue()`.                                                        │
│                                                                                            │
│ The root cause is that the VPlan unrolling logic incorrectly uses `getZExtValue()` to      │
│ retrieve the step value of an induction variable. For a negative step value represented in │
│ a type wider than 64 bits (e.g., `i65 -1`), `getZExtValue()` fails because the value       │
│ cannot be represented as a `uint64_t`.                                                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to use `getSExtValue()` instead, which correctly handles signed step values of  │
│ any bit width by sign-extending the value. This change is applied in `VPlanUnroll.cpp`     │
│ where the unrolled induction variable steps are calculated.                                │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```diff                                                                                    │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanUnroll.cpp                                        │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanUnroll.cpp                                        │
│ @@ -169,7 +169,7 @@                                                                        │
│      // Unroll the induction.                                                              │
│      for (unsigned I = 1; I < UF; ++I) {                                                   │
│        Constant *RuntimeStep =                                                             │
│ -          ConstantInt::get(StepC->getType(), I * StepC->getZExtValue());                  │
│ +          ConstantInt::get(StepC->getType(), I * StepC->getSExtValue());                  │
│        Value *AddTo = LiveOuts[I - 1];                                                     │
│        Value *NextVal = Builder.CreateAdd(AddTo, RuntimeStep, "induction");                │
│        LiveOuts.push_back(NextVal);                                                        │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
